
# Hybrid Topology

## Description
The hybrid topology combines two or more basic topologies (e.g., star + bus, or star + ring) to meet specific network needs.

## Characteristics
- Flexible and scalable for large networks.
- More complex to design and maintain.
- Provides redundancy and adaptability.

## Files
- `hybrid_topology.pkt` → Packet Tracer simulation file.
- `hybrid_topology.png` → Screenshot of the topology.
